      <title>1847 Mar. 15, Carthage, Tennessee [to] Bromfield S. Ridley / A[dam] Fergusson</title>
   </titleInfo>
   <abstract>This is a letter from Adam Fergusson to Bromfield S. Ridley, dated March 15, 1847. Fergusson is writing on behalf of two of his nephews. They have both applied for the position of clerk and master of Chancery Court in Macon County. Fergusson gives his opinion that either will be a fine candidate, although he only describes the accomplishments of one.</abstract>
